  "description": [
    "CAPT Finnigan To Become 41st NavSta CO CAPT Oliver D Finnigan Jr whose naval career has run the gamut from duty in battlewagons to Executive Officer of the De partment of Electrical Engineer ing at the Naval Academy is scheduled to relieve CAPT James D Collett as the Naval Stations Commanding Officer in ceremo nies this afternoon on Dewey Field CAPT Finnigan whose last Newport tour was as a student at the Naval War College here in 194748 will become the Naval Stations 41st Commanding Of ficer A holder of the Bronze Star Medal with Combat V the Air Medal Presidential Unit Citation and the Navy Unit Commenda DriveSaf e School Commences New Class Each Week The Naval Stations DRIVE SAFE School now convenes class es each Monday at 0900 on the lower deck of Bldg 106 Each class lasts two hours and runs for five consecutive days Personnel under 25 years of age reporting to the NavSta for duty and who have not completed the 10hour DRIVESAFE course will be scheduled for class attendance within 30 days of their reporting aboard Commands within the Newport Complex including forces afloat may request quotas for the course by calling extension 3567"
